<item>
            <title>[TIKA-4505] CharsetDetector.getReader returns null when an exception documented</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-4505</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The CharsetDetector.getReader() javadoc states that it will &quot;Raise an exception if no charsets appear to match the input data.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, if CharsetDetector.detect() returns null, null is returned from the method.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In addition, if an IOException occurs it is caught and null is returned from the method.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The documentation does not reference null as a possible return value.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is the underlying cause of an issue in RAT.&#160;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/RAT-494&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/RAT-494&lt;/a&gt; where a document is mentioned.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have requested access to the document in question, if I get access and have permission to distribute the file I will attach it here if you wish.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
